TITLE: Passing Cookies to New Context in Puppeteer
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows how to create a new incognito browser context in Puppeteer, set previously retrieved cookies, and navigate to a page while maintaining logged-in status.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apify/apify-docs/blob/master/sources/academy/webscraping/puppeteer_playwright/common_use_cases/logging_into_a_website.md#2025-04-18_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// Create a fresh non-persistent browser context
const sendEmailContext = await browser.createIncognitoBrowserContext();
// Create a new page on the new browser context and set its cookies
// to be the same ones from the page we used to log into the website.
const page2 = await sendEmailContext.newPage();
await page2.setCookie(...cookies);

// Notice that we are logged in, even though we didn't
// go through the logging in process again!
await page2.goto('https://mail.yahoo.com/');
await page2.waitForTimeout(10000);
```

