TITLE: Parsing Product Variant Prices with Python
DESCRIPTION: This function parses the variant name and price from a given variant text. It splits the text into name and price, removes currency symbols and commas, and converts the price to a Decimal object.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apify/apify-docs/blob/master/sources/academy/webscraping/scraping_basics_python/11_scraping_variants.md#2025-04-18_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
def parse_variant(variant):
    text = variant.text.strip()
    name, price_text = text.split(" - ")
    price = Decimal(
        price_text
        .replace("$", "")
        .replace(",", "")
    )
    return {"variant_name": name, "price": price}
```

