TITLE: Product Data Parser Function
DESCRIPTION: Function that parses product information from a BeautifulSoup element, extracting title and price data.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apify/apify-docs/blob/master/sources/academy/webscraping/scraping_basics_python/09_getting_links.md#2025-04-18_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
def parse_product(product):
    title = product.select_one(".product-item__title").text.strip()

    price_text = (
        product
        .select_one(".price")
        .contents[-1]
        .strip()
        .replace("$", "")
        .replace(",", "")
    )
    if price_text.startswith("From "):
        min_price = Decimal(price_text.removeprefix("From "))
        price = None
    else:
        min_price = Decimal(price_text)
        price = min_price

    return {"title": title, "min_price": min_price, "price": price}
```

