TITLE: Using PuppeteerCrawler with Proxy Configuration and Session Management
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use PuppeteerCrawler with proxy configuration and session pooling. The crawler makes requests to proxy.apify.com endpoints while using a single session to maintain the same IP address across requests.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apify/apify-docs/blob/master/sources/platform/proxy/datacenter_proxy.md#2025-04-18_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { Actor } from 'apify';
import { PuppeteerCrawler } from 'crawlee';

await Actor.init();

const proxyConfiguration = await Actor.createProxyConfiguration();

const crawler = new PuppeteerCrawler({
    proxyConfiguration,
    sessionPoolOptions: { maxPoolSize: 1 },
    async requestHandler({ page }) {
        console.log(await page.content());
    },
});

await crawler.run([
    'https://proxy.apify.com/?format=json',
    'https://proxy.apify.com',
]);

await Actor.exit();
```

