TITLE: Modifying Request URL with Puppeteer
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to intercept and modify a request URL in Puppeteer, changing the destination from one SoundCloud profile to another.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apify/apify-docs/blob/master/sources/academy/webscraping/puppeteer_playwright/reading_intercepting_requests.md#2025-04-18_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import puppeteer from 'puppeteer';

const browser = await puppeteer.launch({ headless: false });
const page = await browser.newPage();

await page.setRequestInterception(true);

// Listen for all requests
page.on('request', async (req) => {
    // If it doesn't match, continue the route normally
    if (!/soundcloud.com\/tiesto/.test(req.url())) return req.continue();
    // Otherwise, continue  the route, but replace "tiesto"
    // in the URL with "mestomusic"
    await req.continue({ url: req.url().replace('tiesto', 'mestomusic') });
});

await page.goto('https://soundcloud.com/tiesto/following');

await page.waitForTimeout(10000);
await browser.close();
```

