TITLE: Extracting Title, Description, and Modified Date Using Puppeteer
DESCRIPTION: Completes the data extraction by adding the Actor's last modification date. The code selects a time element, extracts its datetime attribute which contains a timestamp, then converts it to a JavaScript Date object.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apify/apify-docs/blob/master/sources/academy/tutorials/apify_scrapers/puppeteer_scraper.md#2025-04-18_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
async function pageFunction(context) {
    const { page } = context;
    const title = await page.$eval(
        'header h1',
        ((el) => el.textContent),
    );
    const description = await page.$eval(
        'header span.actor-description',
        ((el) => el.textContent),
    );

    const modifiedTimestamp = await page.$eval(
        'ul.ActorHeader-stats time',
        (el) => el.getAttribute('datetime'),
    );
    const modifiedDate = new Date(Number(modifiedTimestamp));

    return {
        title,
        description,
        modifiedDate,
    };
}
```

