TITLE: Charging for Events in Pay-per-event (PPE) Model using JavaScript SDK
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to use the Apify JavaScript SDK to charge for events in the Pay-per-event (PPE) pricing model. It demonstrates using the Actor.charge() method and handling the ChargeResult.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apify/apify-docs/blob/master/sources/platform/actors/publishing/monetize.mdx#2025-04-18_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const Apify = require('apify');

Apify.main(async () => {
    const chargeResult = await Apify.Actor.charge({
        eventName: 'ACTOR_START',
        amount: 1, // charge $1 for starting the Actor
        idempotencyKey: 'unique-key-for-this-run'
    });

    if (chargeResult.error) {
        console.error('Charging failed:', chargeResult.error);
        return;
    }

    if (chargeResult.maxReached) {
        console.log('Maximum cost per run reached. Stopping the Actor.');
        return;
    }

    // Continue with Actor logic
});
```

