TITLE: Implementing PuppeteerCrawler with Infinite Scroll
DESCRIPTION: Final implementation using PuppeteerCrawler with infinite scroll to handle lazy-loaded images and extract all product data correctly.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apify/apify-docs/blob/master/sources/academy/tutorials/node_js/dealing_with_dynamic_pages.md#2025-04-18_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { PuppeteerCrawler, Dataset, utils } from 'crawlee';

const BASE_URL = 'https://demo-webstore.apify.org';

const crawler = new PuppeteerCrawler({
    requestHandler: async ({ page, parseWithCheerio, request }) => {
        // Scroll to the bottom of the page to load all products
        await utils.puppeteer.infiniteScroll(page, { timeoutSecs: 10 });

        // Now that everything is loaded, we can grab the HTML content
        const $ = await parseWithCheerio();

        const products = $('a[href*="/product/"]');

        const results = [...products].map((product) => {
            const elem = $(product);

            const title = elem.find('h3').text();
            const price = elem.find('div[class*="price"]').text();
            const image = elem.find('img[src]').attr('src');

            return {
                title,
                price,
                image: new URL(image, BASE_URL).href,
            };
        });

        // Save the results to the dataset
        await Dataset.pushData(results);
    },
});

await crawler.run([{ url: 'https://demo-webstore.apify.org/search/new-arrivals' }]);
```

