TITLE: Finding Last Page Number - Puppeteer Implementation
DESCRIPTION: Script using Puppeteer to determine the total number of pages by extracting the last page number from GitHub's pagination.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apify/apify-docs/blob/master/sources/academy/webscraping/puppeteer_playwright/common_use_cases/paginating_through_results.md#2025-04-18_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import puppeteer from 'puppeteer';

const repositories = [];
const BASE_URL = 'https://github.com';
const REPOSITORIES_URL = `${BASE_URL}/orgs/facebook/repositories`;

const browser = await puppeteer.launch({ headless: false });
const firstPage = await browser.newPage();
await firstPage.goto(REPOSITORIES_URL);

const lastPageLabel = await firstPage.$eval(
    'a[aria-label*="Page "]:nth-last-child(2)',
    (element) => element.getAttribute('aria-label'),
);
const lastPageNumber = Number(lastPageLabel.replace(/\D/g, ''));
console.log(lastPageNumber);

await browser.close();
```

